This paper deals with email encryption and privacy, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves designing and implementing a cryptographic protocol, which could fall under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR) or distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the overhead and cost of implementing the protocol, which could fall under the categories of computer systems (cs.SE) or databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper deals with the compatibility of provider-supplied functions with end-to-end encryption, which could fall under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
